            . I am a <rs id="t18210912-177-viclabel1034" type="occupation">fishmonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210912-177-victim1804 t18210912-177-viclabel1034"></join>, and live at <placeName id="t18210912-177-crimeloc1035">Hackney</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18210912-177-crimeloc1035" type="placeName" value="Hackney"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18210912-177-crimeloc1035" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210912-177-off1032 t18210912-177-crimeloc1035"></join>. On the 12th or 13th of September, I marked my money and put it on my desk in the parlour. The prisoner has lived five or six years with me, I suspected him, as he dressed a good deal - I marked the shillings and halfpence in the evening, and next morning 1 s. 7 d. was gone. I sent for an officer, who searched him - he gave me a key of his box from his pocket, which I tried to my desk, it fitted it perfectly well, he then gave me some silver from his waistcoat pocket, 2 s. of which I knew, and in his coat pocket three halfpence were found, which I had marked - he had no occasion to go to the desk.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210912-177-person1806">
                  JOHN 
                  GARVA
               <interp inst="t18210912-177-person1806" type="surname" value="GARVA"></interp>
